data.title: Indian Capital Technology Center
data.text:
Breadmaking is a great tradition and has recently become the "thing to do". In this hands-on class, you will learn to make simple bread selections from scratch, using yeast, butter and water as your main ingredients. Come join the fun and enjoy tasting what you make and take some home for others to try.

Discover the art of crafting beautiful quilts. During this hands-on class you will learn the fundamental skills of quilt making. You will learn tips on selecting fabric, proper use of the rotary cutter, mat and ruler, and learn how to use the tools to cut accurately. You will gain helpful tips on fabric selection, reading the pattern, stitching, and strip piecing. You will also learn the skill of how to place quilt bloscks together, the method of sandwiching the top and back batting and how to bind the quilt.

All students are required to bring their own sewing machine. Additional supply charges may apply, but these will be discussed during the first class session and time allowed to go purchase necessary materials. The instructor may contact you prior to the start of class.

Embrace the homestay staples of the south in this hands-on cooking class with Ms. LaDonna. Learn some simple dishes that pack the flavor of the south. Start with golden, sweet cornbread before you begin preparing smoky ham hock collard greens and southern sweet candied yams. Get down on some crispy fried chicken and creamy mac and cheese that will melt your heart. Come prepared to take some of these wonderful dishes home with you by bringing to go containers.

Unlock the art of storytelling through Creative Writing. In this class, we will dive into the worlds of fiction and literary non-fiction as we explore essential techniques like dramatization, point of view, and characterization. You'll craft one short story and one creative nonfiction piece, refining your voice through peer workshops. By the end, you'll have 25 pages of polished, original work that showcases your unique narrative style.

Old office tools are a changin, with that comes the need for new learning of web-based tools. One of the most popular is Google Workspace formerly known as G Suite. In this class Dr. Synar will show you how to get started with Google Workspace. She will introduce you to Gmail, Meet, Calendar, Chat, Docs, Sheets, Slides, Keep, Sites, Forms, Meets, My Drive, and more. Come prepared to engage in an active, engaging class.
